&lt;p&gt;BAND 6 – FULL TIME (1 WTE) TB CLINICAL NURSE SPECIALIST&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although TB has been around since the beginning of time it is a disease that should be eradicated. The WHO has targeted an end to the TB endemic by 2030 and we are looking for a dynamic nurse to help us in this cause.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A rare and exciting opportunity has arisen to join a small specialist TB team based in Essex. The post-holder will work as part of the TB nursing team running nurse led clinics across our four hospital sites. The role will also include: home visits, managing a varied caseload, education and training and raising awareness of TB. You will help to provide a flexible and responsive high quality TB service facilitating effective patient management and protection to the general public.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic registered nurse ideally with post-registration experience in TB and/or experience in Tuberculin testing and BCG vaccination. You will be expected to work flexibly and autonomously but also function well within a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is full time excluding Bank Holidays and weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If this sounds interesting to you and you want to work in an exciting environment where every day is different, we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits with working for EPUT:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Season Ticket Loans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts for staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Training facilities and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work bank shifts and expand knowledge and experience in other areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary Sacrifice schemes including lease cars and Cycle to Work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Buying and Selling annual leave scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Andrew Hare, TB team leader.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Andrew.hare@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
